## 11. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| AI makes incorrect payment prioritization | High | Mandatory human approval before any payment execution; rollback within 60 seconds |
| Bank API availability or latency issues | High | Circuit breaker pattern; fallback to manual payment flow with pre-filled data |
| Data privacy breach or financial data leak | High | Zero-trust infra, AES-256 encryption, regular penetration testing, bug bounty program |
| Low SME trust in AI for financial actions | Medium | Explainability-first UI; always show agent reasoning; gradual trust onboarding (suggest before execute) |
| Regulatory changes by RBI on AI-driven payments | Medium | Legal team monitoring; modular compliance layer that can be updated independently |

## 12. Evaluation Alignment

| Criterion | How PaykaroBRO AI Delivers |
|---|---|
| Business Value | Directly addresses Rs 4T+ in SME cash flow losses annually; clear monetization via SaaS + transaction fee model |
| Innovation | First multi-agent AI system to close the loop from financial insight to autonomous payment execution in Indian SME context |
| Scalability | Cloud-native on AWS; stateless agents; horizontal scaling to 100K+ concurrent businesses with no architectural changes |
| Implementability | MVP scoped to 3 core agents + dashboard, buildable in 8 weeks; phased roadmap with clear milestones and go/no-go criteria |

